<hr>

<h2>Welcome</h2>

<p>
Welcome to our Nutrition Month webpage! This page was created to help everyone
learn more about the importance of eating healthy foods and living a healthy
lifestyle. Nutrition Month reminds us that making healthy choices every day can
help us become stronger, happier, and more active. By learning about proper
nutrition, we can improve our health and encourage others to do the same.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>About Nutrition Month</h2>

<p>
Nutrition Month is celebrated every July in the Philippines. It is a special
celebration that promotes proper nutrition and healthy eating habits among
Filipinos. Schools, communities, and organizations conduct different activities
to encourage children and adults to choose healthier foods and practice healthy
living every day.
</p>

<p>
Many schools celebrate Nutrition Month by holding poster-making contests,
slogan-writing contests, cooking demonstrations, quiz bees, fun games,
exhibits, and nutrition seminars. These activities help students understand
that eating healthy foods is an important part of staying strong and healthy.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Why Is Good Nutrition Important?</h2>

<p>
Good nutrition gives our body the nutrients it needs to grow, repair itself,
and stay healthy. Eating balanced meals helps children grow properly and gives
them enough energy for school, sports, and other activities.
</p>

<p>
Healthy eating also helps improve concentration, memory, and learning. It
strengthens our immune system, making it easier for our bodies to fight
illnesses. Choosing healthy foods today helps us build a healthier future.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Go Foods</h2>

<p>
Go foods give our body energy to work, study, play, and exercise. They are
rich in carbohydrates and help us stay active throughout the day.
</p>

<p>
Examples of Go foods are rice, bread, corn, potatoes, cereals, oatmeal,
and pasta.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Grow Foods</h2>

<p>
Grow foods help build strong muscles, bones, and body tissues. These foods
contain protein, which is important for children's growth and development.
</p>

<p>
Examples of Grow foods are fish, chicken, eggs, milk, cheese, meat, beans,
and tofu.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Glow Foods</h2>

<p>
Glow foods are rich in vitamins and minerals that keep our body healthy.
They help improve our eyesight, protect us from diseases, and keep our skin
healthy.
</p>

<p>
Examples of Glow foods are carrots, tomatoes, spinach, broccoli, bananas,
mangoes, oranges, apples, and many other fruits and vegetables.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Healthy Habits</h2>

<p>
Eat a balanced meal every day.<br>
Drink at least eight glasses of water.<br>
Eat more fruits and vegetables.<br>
Exercise regularly.<br>
Limit junk food and sugary drinks.<br>
Get enough sleep every night.<br>
Always eat breakfast before going to school.<br>
Wash your hands before eating.<br>
Choose healthy snacks instead of chips and candy.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Benefits of Healthy Eating</h2>

<p>
Healthy eating helps us grow taller and stronger. It gives us energy for
schoolwork, sports, and playing with our friends. It also improves our
memory, concentration, and mood.
</p>

<p>
Proper nutrition lowers the risk of sickness and helps us maintain a healthy
body weight. Eating nutritious foods every day allows us to live a more active
and enjoyable life.
</p>

<hr>

<h2>Our Message</h2>

<p>
Good nutrition is one of the best gifts we can give ourselves. Every healthy
meal we eat is a step toward a stronger body and a brighter future. Let us
celebrate Nutrition Month by making healthy food choices, staying active,
and encouraging our family and friends to live a healthy lifestyle.
</p>

<p>
Remember, healthy habits begin with small choices. Eating nutritious food,
drinking enough water, exercising regularly, and getting enough rest can make
a big difference in our lives. Together, we can build a healthier school,
community, and nation.
</p>

